146
147SSLTranscript::SSLTranscript() {}
148
149SSLTranscript::~SSLTranscript() {}
150
151bool SSLTranscript::Init() {
152 buffer_.reset(BUF_MEM_new());
153 if (!buffer_) {
154 return false;
155 }
156
157 hash_.Reset();
158 return true;
159}
160
161// InitDigestWithData calls |EVP_DigestInit_ex| on |ctx| with |md| and then
162// writes the data in |buf| to it.
163static bool InitDigestWithData(EVP_MD_CTX *ctx, const EVP_MD *md,
164 const BUF_MEM *buf) {
165 if (!EVP_DigestInit_ex(ctx, md, NULL)) {
166 return false;
167 }
168 EVP_DigestUpdate(ctx, buf->data, buf->length);
169 return true;
170}
171
172bool SSLTranscript::InitHash(uint16_t version, const SSL_CIPHER *cipher) {
173 const EVP_MD *md = ssl_get_handshake_digest(version, cipher);
174 return InitDigestWithData(hash_.get(), md, buffer_.get());
175}
176
177void SSLTranscript::FreeBuffer() {
178 buffer_.reset();
179}
180
181size_t SSLTranscript::DigestLen() const {
182 return EVP_MD_size(Digest());
183}
184
185const EVP_MD *SSLTranscript::Digest() const {
186 return EVP_MD_CTX_md(hash_.get());
187}
188
189bool SSLTranscript::UpdateForHelloRetryRequest() {
190 if (buffer_) {
191 buffer_->length = 0;
192 }
193
194 uint8_t old_hash[EVP_MAX_MD_SIZE];
195 size_t hash_len;
196 if (!GetHash(old_hash, &hash_len)) {
197 return false;
198 }
199 const uint8_t header[4] = {SSL3_MT_MESSAGE_HASH, 0, 0,
200 static_cast<uint8_t>(hash_len)};
201 if (!EVP_DigestInit_ex(hash_.get(), Digest(), nullptr) ||
202 !Update(header) ||
203 !Update(MakeConstSpan(old_hash, hash_len))) {
204 return false;
205 }
206 return true;
207}
208
209bool SSLTranscript::CopyToHashContext(EVP_MD_CTX *ctx, const EVP_MD *digest) {
210 const EVP_MD *transcript_digest = Digest();
211 if (transcript_digest != nullptr &&
212 EVP_MD_type(transcript_digest) == EVP_MD_type(digest)) {
213 return EVP_MD_CTX_copy_ex(ctx, hash_.get());
214 }
215
216 if (buffer_) {
217 return EVP_DigestInit_ex(ctx, digest, nullptr) &&
218 EVP_DigestUpdate(ctx, buffer_->data, buffer_->length);
219 }
220
221 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_INTERNAL_ERROR);
222 return false;
223}
224
225bool SSLTranscript::Update(Span<const uint8_t> in) {
226 // Depending on the state of the handshake, either the handshake buffer may be
227 // active, the rolling hash, or both.
228 if (buffer_ &&
229 !BUF_MEM_append(buffer_.get(), in.data(), in.size())) {
230 return false;
231 }
232
233 if (EVP_MD_CTX_md(hash_.get()) != NULL) {
234 EVP_DigestUpdate(hash_.get(), in.data(), in.size());
235 }
236
237 return true;
238}
239
240bool SSLTranscript::GetHash(uint8_t *out, size_t *out_len) {
241 ScopedEVP_MD_CTX ctx;
242 unsigned len;
243 if (!EVP_MD_CTX_copy_ex(ctx.get(), hash_.get()) ||
244 !EVP_DigestFinal_ex(ctx.get(), out, &len)) {
245 return false;
246 }
247 *out_len = len;
248 return true;
249}
250
251bool SSLTranscript::GetFinishedMAC(uint8_t *out, size_t *out_len,
252 const SSL_SESSION *session,
253 bool from_server) {
254 static const char kClientLabel[] = "client finished";
255 static const char kServerLabel[] = "server finished";
256 auto label = from_server
257 ? MakeConstSpan(kServerLabel, sizeof(kServerLabel) - 1)
258 : MakeConstSpan(kClientLabel, sizeof(kClientLabel) - 1);
259
260 uint8_t digest[EVP_MAX_MD_SIZE];
261 size_t digest_len;
262 if (!GetHash(digest, &digest_len)) {
263 return false;
264 }
265
266 static const size_t kFinishedLen = 12;
267 if (!tls1_prf(Digest(), MakeSpan(out, kFinishedLen),
268 MakeConstSpan(session->secret, session->secret_length), label,
269 MakeConstSpan(digest, digest_len), {})) {
270 return false;
271 }
272
273 *out_len = kFinishedLen;
274 return true;
275}
